<sec id="Sec9" class="sec">
 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Singular Value Decomposition of a bivariate predictors’ space; derivation of Eqs. (
  <a rid="Equ1" ref-type="" href="#Equ1">1</a>)–(
  <a rid="Equ5" ref-type="" href="#Equ5">5</a>)
 </div>
 <p id="Par23" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">We centralize our predictors, denote them 
  <span class="italic">x</span>
  <sub>
   <span class="bold">1</span>
  </sub> and 
  <span class="italic">x</span>
  <sub>
   <span class="bold">2</span>
  </sub>, respectively, arrange them column-wise in matrix 
  <span class="bold">X</span> = [
  <span class="bold">x</span>
  <sub>1</sub>
  <span class="bold">x</span>
  <sub>2</sub>], and perform the SVD of 
  <span class="bold">X</span> in the form of Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ7" ref-type="" href="#Equ7">7</a>). The columns of matrix 
  <span class="bold">P</span> = [
  <span class="bold">p</span>
  <sub>1</sub> 
  <span class="bold">p</span>
  <sub>2</sub>], called singular vectors, are obtained from the columns of 
  <span class="bold">X</span> by an orthogonal rotation with 2x2 matrix 
  <span class="bold">E</span>, followed by their normalization by the square roots of diagonal elements of 2x2 matrix 
  <span class="bold">Λ</span>:
  <div id="Equ9" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">9</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M23" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \mathbf{P}=\mathbf{XE}{\boldsymbol{\Lambda}}^{-1/2} $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M24" display="block" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="bold" class="mi">P</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span mathvariant="bold" class="mi">XE</span>
     <div class="msup">
      <span mathvariant="bold" class="mi">Λ</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mn">1</span>
       <span class="mo">/</span>
       <span class="mn">2</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="10584_2018_2341_Article_Equ9.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
 </p>
 <p id="Par24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">By construction, 
  <span class="bold">p</span>
  <sub>1</sub> and 
  <span class="bold">p</span>
  <sub>2</sub> are standardized, mutually uncorrelated time series.
 </p>
 <p id="Par25" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">When there are only two predictors, 
  <span class="italic">x</span>
  <sub>1</sub> and 
  <span class="italic">x</span>
  <sub>2</sub>, it is possible to present the elements of matrices 
  <span class="bold">E</span> and 
  <span class="bold">Λ</span> of the canonical decomposition of the predictors’ variance-covariance matrix 
  <span class="bold">C</span> = 
  <span class="bold">X</span>
  <span class="sup">T</span>
  <span class="bold">X</span>/(
  <span class="italic">n</span> − 1) = 
  <span class="bold">EΛE</span>
  <span class="sup">T</span> as functions of its elements.
 </p>
 <p id="Par26" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Let standard deviations of 
  <span class="italic">x</span>
  <sub>1</sub> and 
  <span class="italic">x</span>
  <sub>2</sub> be 
  <span class="italic">σ</span>
  <sub>1</sub> and 
  <span class="italic">σ</span>
  <sub>2</sub>, respectively, and their correlation coefficient be 
  <span class="italic">ρ</span>, then their variance-covariance matrix is:
  <div id="Equ10" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">10</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M25" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \mathbf{C}=\left[\begin{array}{cc}{\sigma}_1^2&amp; \rho {\sigma}_1{\sigma}_2\\ {}\rho {\sigma}_1{\sigma}_2&amp; {\sigma}_2^2\end{array}\right]. $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M26" display="block" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="bold" class="mi">C</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mtable">
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <div class="msubsup">
          <span class="mi">σ</span>
          <span class="mn">1</span>
          <span class="mn">2</span>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mi">ρ</span>
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">σ</span>
          <span class="mn">1</span>
         </div>
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">σ</span>
          <span class="mn">2</span>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mi">ρ</span>
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">σ</span>
          <span class="mn">1</span>
         </div>
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">σ</span>
          <span class="mn">2</span>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <div class="msubsup">
          <span class="mi">σ</span>
          <span class="mn">2</span>
          <span class="mn">2</span>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">.</span>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="10584_2018_2341_Article_Equ10.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
 </p>
 <p id="Par27" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Note that:
  <div id="Equc" class="disp-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M27" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \mathbf{C}=\frac{\sigma_1^2+{\sigma}_2^2}{2}\ \mathbf{I}+{\left[{\left(\frac{\sigma_1^2+{\sigma}_2^2}{2}\right)}^2+{\rho}^2{\sigma}_1^2{\sigma}_2^2\right]}^{1/2}\left[\begin{array}{cc}\cos 2\phi &amp; \sin 2\phi \\ {}\sin 2\phi &amp; -\cos 2\phi \end{array}\right], $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M28" display="block" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="bold" class="mi">C</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mi">σ</span>
        <span class="mn">1</span>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">+</span>
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mi">σ</span>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mn">2</span>
     </div>
     <span width="0.25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="bold" class="mi">I</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <div class="msup">
      <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
       <div class="mrow">
        <div class="msup">
         <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
          <div class="mfrac">
           <div class="mrow">
            <div class="msubsup">
             <span class="mi">σ</span>
             <span class="mn">1</span>
             <span class="mn">2</span>
            </div>
            <span class="mo">+</span>
            <div class="msubsup">
             <span class="mi">σ</span>
             <span class="mn">2</span>
             <span class="mn">2</span>
            </div>
           </div>
           <span class="mn">2</span>
          </div>
         </div>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
        </div>
        <span class="mo">+</span>
        <div class="msup">
         <span class="mi">ρ</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
        </div>
        <div class="msubsup">
         <span class="mi">σ</span>
         <span class="mn">1</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
        </div>
        <div class="msubsup">
         <span class="mi">σ</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mn">1</span>
       <span class="mo">/</span>
       <span class="mn">2</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mtable">
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">cos</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">sin</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">sin</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <span class="mo">cos</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">,</span>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="10584_2018_2341_Article_Equc.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>where 
  <span class="bold">I</span> is a 2x2 identity matrix, and 
  <span class="italic">ϕ</span> from the interval [0, 
  <span class="italic">π</span>) is determined by:
  <div id="Equ11" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">11</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M29" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \cot \left(2\phi \right)=\left({\sigma}_1^2-{\sigma}_2^2\right)/\left(2\rho {\sigma}_1{\sigma}_2\right). $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M30" display="block" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mo">cot</span>
     <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mn">2</span>
       <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mi">σ</span>
        <span class="mn">1</span>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mi">σ</span>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">/</span>
     <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mn">2</span>
       <span class="mi">ρ</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">σ</span>
        <span class="mn">1</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">σ</span>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">.</span>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="10584_2018_2341_Article_Equ11.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
 </p>
 <p id="Par28" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Introducing a non-dimensional parameter 
  <span class="italic">k</span> = 
  <span class="italic">σ</span>
  <sub>1</sub>/
  <span class="italic">σ</span>
  <sub>2</sub>, and expressing 
  <span class="italic">ϕ</span> from Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ11" ref-type="" href="#Equ11">11</a>) as a function of 
  <span class="italic">k</span> and 
  <span class="italic">ρ</span>, we obtain Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ3" ref-type="" href="#Equ3">3</a>).
 </p>
 <p id="Par29" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Using the identity:
  <div id="Equd" class="disp-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M31" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \left[\begin{array}{cc}\;\cos 2\phi &amp; \sin 2\phi \\ {}\sin 2\phi &amp; -\cos 2\phi \end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{cc}\;\cos \phi &amp; -\sin \phi \\ {}\sin \phi &amp; \kern0.24em \cos \phi \end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{cc}1&amp; 0\\ {}0&amp; -1\end{array}\right]{\left[\begin{array}{cc}\cos \phi &amp; -\sin \phi \\ {}\sin \phi &amp; \cos \phi \end{array}\right]}^T $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M32" display="block" class="math">
     <div close="]" open="[" separators="," class="mfenced">
      <div class="mtable">
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span width="0.12em" class="mspace"/>
         <span class="mo">cos</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">sin</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">sin</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <span class="mo">cos</span>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div close="]" open="[" separators="," class="mfenced">
      <div class="mtable">
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span width="0.12em" class="mspace"/>
         <span class="mo">cos</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <span class="mo">sin</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">sin</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span width="0.24em" class="mspace"/>
         <span class="mo">cos</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div close="]" open="[" separators="," class="mfenced">
      <div class="mtable">
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mn">1</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mn">0</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mn">0</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <span class="mn">1</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="msup">
      <div close="]" open="[" separators="," class="mfenced">
       <div class="mtable">
        <div class="mtr">
         <div class="mtd">
          <span class="mo">cos</span>
          <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
         </div>
         <div class="mtd">
          <span class="mo">−</span>
          <span class="mo">sin</span>
          <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mtr">
         <div class="mtd">
          <span class="mo">sin</span>
          <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
         </div>
         <div class="mtd">
          <span class="mo">cos</span>
          <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mi">T</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="10584_2018_2341_Article_Equd.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>we rewrite:
  <div id="Eque" class="disp-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M33" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \mathbf{C}=\left[\begin{array}{cc}\cos \phi &amp; -\sin \phi \\ {}\sin \phi &amp; \cos \phi \end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{cc}{\lambda}_1&amp; 0\\ {}0&amp; {\lambda}_2\end{array}\right]{\left[\begin{array}{cc}\cos \phi &amp; -\sin \phi \\ {}\sin \phi &amp; \cos \phi \end{array}\right]}^T $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M34" display="block" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="bold" class="mi">C</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mtable">
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">cos</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <span class="mo">sin</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">sin</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mo">cos</span>
         <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
      <div class="mtable">
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">λ</span>
          <span class="mn">1</span>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mn">0</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="mtr">
        <div class="mtd">
         <span class="mn">0</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mtd">
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">λ</span>
          <span class="mn">2</span>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="msup">
      <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
       <div class="mtable">
        <div class="mtr">
         <div class="mtd">
          <span class="mo">cos</span>
          <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
         </div>
         <div class="mtd">
          <span class="mo">−</span>
          <span class="mo">sin</span>
          <span class="mi">ϕ</span>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mtr">
         <div class="mtd">
          <span class="mo">sin</span>
