     </div>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="10584_2018_2341_Article_Equ12.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
 </p>
 <p id="Par30" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">where 
  <span class="italic">ϕ</span> is given by Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ3" ref-type="" href="#Equ3">3</a>) and 
  <span class="italic">λ</span>
  <sub>1</sub> and 
  <span class="italic">λ</span>
  <sub>2</sub> by Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ4" ref-type="" href="#Equ4">4</a>).
 </p>
 <p id="Par31" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Inserting expressions for 
  <span class="bold">E</span> and 
  <span class="bold">Λ</span> from Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ12" ref-type="" href="#Equ12">12</a>) into Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ9" ref-type="" href="#Equ9">9</a>), we write them out in the component form for an arbitrary row of matrix P to obtain Eqs. (
  <a rid="Equ1" ref-type="" href="#Equ1">1</a>)–(
  <a rid="Equ2" ref-type="" href="#Equ2">2</a>).
 </p>
 <p id="Par32" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Preisendorfer (
  <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR43" href="#CR43">1988</a>) noted that Eqs. (
  <a rid="Equ11" ref-type="" href="#Equ11">11</a>) and (
  <a rid="Equ4" ref-type="" href="#Equ4">4</a>) are known since Pearson (
  <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR42" href="#CR42">1901</a>). Equation (
  <a rid="Equ3" ref-type="" href="#Equ3">3</a>) derived above gives an explicit form for the angle 
  <span class="italic">ϕ</span>, expressing it through the non-dimensional parameters 
  <span class="italic">k</span> and 
  <span class="italic">ρ</span> of the original predictors’ variance-covariance matrix, making it more convenient for interpretation. A traditional non-dimensional parameter of such matrix for SVD-based predictors 
  <span class="italic">p</span>
  <sub>1</sub>, 
  <span class="italic">p</span>
  <sub>2</sub>, the portion of variance explained by one of the predictors, follows from Eq. (
  <a rid="Equ4" ref-type="" href="#Equ4">4</a>). For 
  <span class="italic">p</span>
  <sub>1</sub>, it is expressed through 
  <span class="italic">k</span> and 
  <span class="italic">ρ</span> as:
  <div id="Equ13" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">13</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M37" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \frac{\lambda_1}{\lambda_1+{\lambda}_2}=\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{2}{\left[{\left(\frac{k-{k}^{-1}}{k+{k}^{-1}}\right)}^2+{\left(\frac{2\rho }{k+{k}^{-1}}\right)}^2\right]}^{1/2}. $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M38" display="block" class="math">
     <div class="mfrac">
      <div class="msub">
       <span class="mi">λ</span>
       <span class="mn">1</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">λ</span>
        <span class="mn">1</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">+</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">λ</span>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <span class="mn">1</span>
      <span class="mn">2</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <div class="mfrac">
      <span class="mn">1</span>
      <span class="mn">2</span>
     </div>
     <div class="msup">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mo">[</span>
       <div class="msup">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mo">(</span>
         <div class="mfrac">
          <div class="mrow">
           <span class="mi">k</span>
           <span class="mo">−</span>
           <div class="msup">
            <div class="mrow">
             <span class="mi">k</span>
            </div>
            <div class="mrow">
             <span class="mo">−</span>
             <span class="mn">1</span>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mrow">
           <span class="mi">k</span>
           <span class="mo">+</span>
           <div class="msup">
            <div class="mrow">
             <span class="mi">k</span>
            </div>
            <div class="mrow">
             <span class="mo">−</span>
             <span class="mn">1</span>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
         <span class="mo">)</span>
        </div>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">+</span>
       <div class="msup">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mo">(</span>
         <div class="mfrac">
          <div class="mrow">
           <span class="mn">2</span>
           <span class="mi">ρ</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mrow">
           <span class="mi">k</span>
           <span class="mo">+</span>
           <div class="msup">
            <div class="mrow">
             <span class="mi">k</span>
            </div>
            <div class="mrow">
             <span class="mo">−</span>
             <span class="mn">1</span>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
         <span class="mo">)</span>
        </div>
        <span class="mn">2</span>
