     <span class="italic">ρ</span> = 0, 
     <span class="italic">k</span> ≥ 1}. In particular, while the definition in Eq. (
     <a rid="Equ3" ref-type="" href="#Equ3">3</a>) made 
     <span class="italic">ϕ</span> right-continuous at 
     <span class="italic">ρ</span> = 0 for all 
     <span class="italic">k</span> &gt; 1, since ϕ(0, 
     <span class="italic">k</span>) = ϕ(0+, 
     <span class="italic">k</span>) = 0, the left limit of 
     <span class="italic">ϕ</span> in these points is different: ϕ(0−, 
