    <div xlink:href="10584_2018_2341_Article_Equf.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>in (
  <span class="italic">x</span>
  <sub>1</sub>, 
  <span class="italic">x</span>
  <sub>2</sub>) coordinates and by equation:
  <div id="Equg" class="disp-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M41" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ {p}_1^2/{\lambda}_1+{p}_2^2/{\lambda}_2=q\left(\alpha \right) $$\end{document}</span>
